Presidential Airways Inc said it willserve 12 cities when it starts operating Continental Expressunder a joint marketing agreement with Texas Air Corp's &lt;TEX>Continental Airlines on March 23.    From its base at Dulles Airport in Washington, Presidentialwill serve Albany, N.Y., Birmingham and Huntsville in Alabama,Columbus, Ohio, Daytona Beach, Melbourne and Sarasota, all inFlorida, Indianapolis, New York's Kennedy Airport,Philadelphia, Portland, Me., and Savannah, Ga.    Under the agreement, Presidential will continue as aseparate company but its mileage plan and other services willbe combined with those of Continental Airlines. Reuter&#3;